<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1592&amp;p=13680#p13680"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[How does the MMC3 detect VBlank?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1592&amp;p=13680#p13680"><![CDATA[
It operates entirely via PPU A12, decrementing once on each rising edge (but ignoring rapid pulses above a certain rate, which allows it to only see one toggle per scanline).<br /><br />The info regarding 42 toggles of A13 was pure speculation and has no basis in reality whatsoever - PPU A13 isn't even <strong>connected</strong> to the MMC3 to begin with.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed May 31, 2006 8:50 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
