I just realized how incoherent the title was, it's now fixed. <br /><br />Is the IRQ counter really paused during Vblank? If so, how? Kevtris' MMC3 page suggests it isn't really a scanline counter at all, just a A12 counter, which would mean it is oblivious to Vblank which of course is reasonable, this however contrasts Martin Korth's info which suggests it counts scanlines by incrementing every 42 A13 toggles, elsewhere I have also heard mention of A13. Which is it?<br /><br />TIA is "thanks in advance", thanks (no more shorthand ;)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Wed May 31, 2006 8:26 pm</p><hr />
